reviews.text: When our local East Of Chicago closed we started getting our pizza here. Taco pizza is amazing. We get the Tower and it has everything. Pepperoni and sausage, ham, bacon,green peppers,onions, banana peppers,green olives, black olives. It's delicious and it lasts three days. The crust is light and airy. The sauce is yummy. This pizza fills you up full üçï. They do sheet pizzas too. The staff is friendly and dedicated to making the best pizzas.

Call today to order and had the rudest. Lady ever answer? Ed the phone didn't even say East to Chicago. Unlike is this East to Chicago? She's like yeah, I said OK and I go to order and then she is this so crappy. I have never had that ever and I have ordered from East Chicago says God probably about the day.  They opened there. This was the rudest woman I've ever had in my life there. It's awful. I'm hoping my delivery in my Pizza is better than her attitude was today.

I typically order a pizza from here at least once a week for my son.  He always gets a large,  well-done pepperoni pizza.  It's always hot and prepared exactly how he likes it.  Staff is always pleasant and courteous both on the phone when I place the order and when I go to pick it up.  They always ask if we need plates and napkins.

BUT..they LOST MY BUSINESS AFTER GOING DOORDASH!!!!!!!!!
I use to buy a medium pizza and would give the delivery person a 5 dollar tip each time. NOW if I door dash it.. it cost me over
$33.33 !!!!!!!!!! I'm NOT paying it!!!!!!!! Edited after getting a response... YOU'RE LYING ABOUT IT ONLY BEING A SUPPLEMENT. YOUR PHONE NUMBER IS OUT OF ORDER AND YET YOU STILL REPLY AS IT ISN'T....LIAR! AND on top of all that.. I can't even order my favorite pizza anymore..pepperoni and mushroom and cheese pizza.. YOU SCREWED UP!
Ordered from this location for the first time today (we don't have one in our neighborhood) the taco pizza was amazing, staff was friendly and the pizzas were loaded up. We'll be back.

detailedReviews.author: Amanda Lower
detailedReviews.text: We ordered for Delivery, One large cheese and two medium taco pizzas. One taco pizza should have been no lettuce no tomato. The other had no tomato but should have had lettuce. I put one in the cart then went back to menu and added the second. It duplicated my pizza and didn't change how it should have been. No big deal so I call. The manager was extremely rude, I only mentioned the taco pizza issue, the cheese pizza also had the cheese stuck to the top of the box and I didn't even mention that. I called the corporate number and spoke to another manager who advised I leave a review and that she had also seen the online ordering have issues before as well. It was such a small thing that our pizza was messed up and didn't appreciate the attitude at all. I have ordered from East Of Chicago a lot and not once have ever called to complain. Was just disappointed in how the manager was. Probably Will not be ordering from this Location again.
